  "local_port": 34966,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Does a user always need to keep the data \u2018ON\u2019 for outgoing/incoming calls on Jio network?",
  "response": "On the Jio network, **you do not need to keep mobile data (cellular data) turned ON** for making or receiving voice calls, provided your device supports **VoLTE (Voice over LTE)** and it is enabled. Here's a concise breakdown:\n\n1. **VoLTE Dependency**:  \n   Jio operates exclusively on 4G LTE for voice calls (no 2G/3G fallback). VoLTE allows voice calls to use the LTE network **without consuming your mobile data plan** or requiring the mobile data toggle to be ON.\n\n2. **Mobile Data Toggle**:  \n   - Turning off mobile data **does not disable VoLTE calls**. The LTE network remains active for voice services.  \n   - However, ensure VoLTE is enabled in your device settings (usually under \"Mobile Network\" or \"Cellular Settings\").\n\n3. **Wi-Fi Calling Alternative**:  \n   If enabled, calls can route over Wi-Fi even without cellular coverage. This also doesn\u2019t require mobile data.\n\n4. **Critical Requirements**:  \n   - A VoLTE-compatible device.  \n   - VoLTE activated on your phone and SIM.  \n   - Strong Jio 4G signal or Wi-Fi (for Wi-Fi calling).\n\n**In short**: As long as VoLTE is configured properly, you can make/receive calls on Jio **without mobile data being turned ON**. The LTE network handles voice independently.",
